  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "0141805e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Train  : 2023-01-01 → 2024-10-02  (641 days)\n",
      "Val    : 2024-10-03 → 2024-11-01  (30 days)\n",
      "Holdout: 2024-11-02 → 2024-12-31  (60 days)  ← SACRED\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ts_pivot, price_daily = data_loading.build_daily_aggregates(perishable)\n",
    "train_dates, val_dates, holdout_dates = data_loading.make_three_way_split(ts_pivot)\n",
    "print(f\"Train  : {train_dates[0].date()} → {train_dates[-1].date()}  ({len(train_dates)} days)\")\n",
    "print(f\"Val    : {val_dates[0].date()} → {val_dates[-1].date()}  ({len(val_dates)} days)\")\n",
    "print(f\"Holdout: {holdout_dates[0].date()} → {holdout_dates[-1].date()}  ({len(holdout_dates)} days)  ← SACRED\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b763d57b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2 · Demand forecasting (Stage 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "Trains LightGBM / Prophet / Holt-Winters on the training window, evaluates on validation, picks the winner by directional accuracy.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Tip:** Prophet is the slowest. The `RUN_PROPHET = False` flag below skips it for the first run. LightGBM still wins regardless — re-run later with `RUN_PROPHET = True` to get the full comparison table."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "60cccb48",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Train rows: 5016, Val rows: 240, Holdout rows: 480\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Toggle Prophet on/off (False = much faster first run)\n",
    "RUN_PROPHET = False\n",
    "\n",
    "feats = features.build_demand_feature_set(\n",
    "    ts_pivot, price_daily, train_dates, val_dates, holdout_dates,\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(f\"Train rows: {len(feats['feat_train'])}, Val rows: {len(feats['feat_val'])}, Holdout rows: {len(feats['feat_holdout'])}\")"
   ]
  },
